    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "question": "An aircraft requires a specific inspection every 500 flight hours or 250 flight cycles, whichever comes first. If the aircraft accumulates 100 flight hours per month and completes 60 flight cycles per month, how many months will pass before this inspection is due?",
    "options": [
      "5.00 months",
      "4.17 months",
      "2.50 months",
      "8.33 months"
    ],
    "correct_answer": "B",
    "correct_answer_text": "4.17 months",
    "explanation": "The inspection is due when the first of the two criteria (flight hours or flight cycles) is met. Calculate the time to reach each threshold independently and then select the minimum duration.",
    "solution_steps": [
      "Formula: $\\text{Time (hours)} = \\frac{\\text{Required hours}}{\\text{Hours per month}}$, $\\text{Time (cycles)} = \\frac{\\text{Required cycles}}{\\text{Cycles per month}}$",
      "Substitute: $\\text{Time (hours)} = \\frac{500\\,\\text{hours}}{100\\,\\text{hours/month}}$, $\\text{Time (cycles)} = \\frac{250\\,\\text{cycles}}{60\\,\\text{cycles/month}}$",
      "Compute: $\\text{Time (hours)} = 5.00\\,\\text{months}$, $\\text{Time (cycles)} \\approx 4.1667\\,\\text{months}$",
      "Compute: The inspection is due at the minimum of these times, which is $4.1667\\,\\text{months}$.",
      "Final: The inspection is due in $4.17\\,\\text{months}$ (rounded to two decimal places)."
    ],
